      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualifications documented separately.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment not required at MRL 2. Analyst qualifications (PhD in computational fluid dynamics, 8 years rotary blood pump CFD experience) documented in team qualification record TQR-2024-07. Simulation execution checklist completed and archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection documented.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on literature consensus for rotary blood pump flows (Hariharan et al. 2011, Fraser et al. 2012). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model applied. Formal model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2 but model selection rationale documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) must be traceable to measurement data or validated reference sources with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry sourced from FDA benchmark CAD files (dataset pump-geometry-mesh-dataset, dataVintage 2025-09-30). Fluid properties (density 1056 kg/m3, dynamic viscosity 3.5e-3 Pa·s) from experimental characterization dataset (experimental-hemolysis-dataset, dataVintage 2025-10-15). All inputs traceable to archived sources. Re-validation against updated geometry inputs is planned following the February 2026 model revision but has not yet been completed; current assessment relies on pre-revision input datasets."
    },
